s illustrate the results and complete some of the proofs. Volume 1 contains all the details on describing generic constructions of units and the subgroup they generate. Volume 2 mainly is about structure theorems and geometric methods. Without being encyclopaedic, all main results and techniques used to achieve these results are included. Basic courses in group theory, ring theory and field theory are assumed as background.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aGroup ringsvTextbooks. 0aRings (Algebra)vTextbooks 0aRings (Algebra)vTextbooks. 0aUnit groups (Ring theory)vTextbooks. 4aGruppentheorie. 7aMATHEMATICS / Group Theory.2bisacsh1 adel Río, Ángel, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2016z978311070100508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2015z9783110439687oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Mathematics 2015z9783110438765oZDB-23-DMA0 cEPUBz97831103861720 cprintz978311037278640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311037294640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110372946423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110372946.jpg  a978-3-11-070100-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MTPY  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MTPY  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2015  aZDB-23-DMAb2015